
<fieldset>
<legend>Need to edit your skills?</legend>
<p>Move the slider along to indicate your proficiency with each skill below.  Not sure where your experience falls?  Here are some guidelines:</p>

<ul id ="needsbullets">
<li><b>0-20:</b>  Some general knowledge but little hands-on experience; only comfortably performing very simple tasks.</li>
<li><b>21-40: </b> Junior level experience; can perform common tasks comfortably but still learing the ropes with more complex or unusual problems.</li>
<li><b>41-60: </b> Solid professional experience; can easily handle any routine tasks, works at a normal pace with few errors, comfortable tackling new tasks. </li>
<li><b>61-80:</b>  Very proficient; easily able to accomplish all reasonable tasks, works very quickly and accurately, sought out by others with questions in this area.</li>
<li><b>81-100:</b>  Exceptional proficiency; more familiar/competent than most other users, develops unique solutions or functionality, known for expertise in area (speaks at conferences, heavily involved in developing new features, etc.)</li>
</ul><br>

	<ul id="skill-list" class="skills-list">
	<% @professional.personal_qualities.each do |pq| %>
		<% if pq.metric.class == Skill %>
		<% @pq = pq %>		
		<% form_for @pq.metric.name.to_sym, @pq, :url => {:action => :update_value}, :html => { :id => @pq.metric.id.to_s+'_form'} do |form| %>
			<%=form.hidden_field :value, { :id => @pq.metric.id.to_s+"_value" } %>
			<%=form.hidden_field :id %>
			<%=hidden_field_tag 'object_name', @pq.metric.name %>
			<li class="skills_list_skill_item" id="skill_<%=@pq.metric.id%>">
				<label class="skillname"><%= pq.metric.display_name %></label>		
					<div class="removeskill"><a id="remove_<%=@pq.metric.id.to_s%>"><%=l(:remove)%></a></div>
				<%= render :partial => 'slider', :locals => {:name => @pq.metric.id, :value => @pq.value} %>
			
			</li>
			<% end %>
	
		<% end %>
	<% end %>
</ul>
<br>
